trans0499: You can make more personalized settings for the wireless network to adapt to various wireless network environments.
trans0501: Wi-Fi channel: The data signal transmission channel that uses wireless signals as the transmission medium. If you choose "Adaptive", the router will choose a best channel according to the surrounding environment.
trans0502: Mode: Set the wireless working mode of the router. 2.4G Wi-Fi recommends using 802.11b/g/n/ax mode. 5G Wi-Fi recommends using 802.11a/n/ac/ax modes.
trans0503: Wi-Fi bandwidth setting: set the channel width occupied by wireless data transmission, the options are 20 MHz, 40 MHz, 20/40 MHz, 80 MHz, 20/40/80 MHz and 20/40/80/160 MHz .
trans0504: Leading Interval Setting: Set the guard interval between the data blocks sent by the router, the options are short interval, medium interval and long interval. When short interval is selected, the router transmission rate can be increased.
trans0505: Wi-Fi Stealth: Hide the name of the SSID. When this function is enabled, wireless clients will not be able to search for this wireless network. To join this wireless network, the name of the SSID must be entered manually to further enhance the security of the wireless network.
trans0506: WMM: When WMM is turned on, the router will have a wireless quality of service feature that improves video and audio application quality for wireless clients.
trans0528: Valid Lifetime should be greater than Preferred Lifetime
trans0531: When you have guests in your home, you can turn on the guest Wi-Fi function. This way, your home will have two separate Wi-Fi networks, the main Wi-Fi and the guest Wi-Fi at the same time. While guests can access the Internet through private Wi-Fi, they cannot manage your router or access devices on your home network. Guest Wi-Fi effectively guarantees your online privacy and security.
trans0532: On Time: The length of time the guest Wi-Fi is open for use. After the set time, the guest Wi-Fi will be automatically turned off.
trans0533: Security: Choose whether to set a password for the guest Wi-Fi network. If you choose "No Encryption", anyone can connect to the network.
trans0534: Guest Wi-Fi Password: Set the password for connecting to the guest Wi-Fi network in encrypted mode.
